# GitHub OSS Workflow

## Before Starting Any Task
1. Use GitHub MCP to fetch the issue or PR details — read the full description, comments, and linked issues.
2. Check if a related PR already exists. If so, read its diff before writing new code.
3. Check if the repo has a `CONTRIBUTING.md` — follow its standards exactly.

## Branch Strategy
- Branch name format: `fix/issue-{number}-short-description` or `feat/issue-{number}-short-description`
- Always branch from the default branch (usually `main` or `develop`).

## PR Checklist (auto-verify before surfacing to user)
- [ ] All existing tests pass
- [ ] New functionality has test coverage consistent with repo's testing strategy
- [ ] Commits follow Conventional Commits format
- [ ] PR description references the issue number with `Closes #N`
- [ ] No debug logs, console.log, or print statements left in code
- [ ] Linter and formatter pass

## Interacting with Issues via GitHub MCP
- Add a comment to the issue when starting work: "Working on a fix for this."
- Reference specific code lines when asking maintainer questions.
